One person was confirmed dead while seven others sustained injuries in an accident involving a Toyota bus and a Fiat Van around Babcock University on Sagamu-Ijebu Ode expressway. <img class="alignnone wp-image-1269190 size-medium" src="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=300%2C172&#038;ssl=1" alt="One dead, seven injured on Sagamu-Ijebu Ode expressway accident" width="300" height="172" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=300%2C172&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=768%2C440&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=1024%2C586&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=58%2C33&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=260%2C149&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=200%2C114&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?resize=560%2C321&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i0.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/Accident.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 300px) 100vw, 300px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> The spokesperson of the Traffic Compliance and Enforcement Corps (TRACE), Mr Babatunde AKIN BIYI confirmed the incident to our Correspondent in Abeokuta on Thursday. The TRACE spokesman added that the accident was caused by reckless driving and loss of control on the part of the bus driver. Akinbiyi noted that the accident occurred around 2:30 am while the bus was driving inbound Lagos from the East. “The driver of the bus drove recklessly, lost control and rammed into the white Fiat van marked LAM 528 LG from behind,” he said. ⤕Six days after, FRSC yet to recover accident victims from Osaso river ⤕Lagos State honours Policewoman who saved robbery victim’s life He explained that the dead victims were the driver of the bus marked AKD 101 XS, while the injured victims were also from the bus. He added that the corpses of the dead had been deposited at Idera Hospital morgue, Sagamu while the injured were taken to Babcock University Teaching Hospital, Ilisan. Vanguard News Nigeria. Five persons were confirmed dead on Tuesday while two others sustained injuries in an accident involving a Subaru car and a Honda bus at Orile Imo area on the Sagamu/Abeokuta expressway. November 27, 2018 In "News" An unidentified motorboy attached to a tanker on Tuesday died after a fatal crash involving three trucks on the Sagamu-Benin expressway in Ogun. August 14, 2018 In "News" ABEOKUTA—An accident involving a white Mazda bus and a Mack truck at Ibara village, along Abeokuta /Sagamu Expressway in Ogun State, yesterday, reportedly claimed the lives of ten people, including a toddler July 7, 2017 In "News"